aine|title=Margaret Atwood, Language, Text, and System|year=1983|publisher=University of British Columbia Press|location=Vancouver|pages=|isbn=978-0-7748-0170-6|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/margaretatwoodla0000unse}}\n* {{cite book|last=Sullivan|first=Rosemary|authorlink=Rosemary Sullivan|title=The Red Shoes: Margaret Atwood Starting Out|year=1998|publisher=HarperFlamingoCanada|location=Toronto|isbn=978-0-00-255423-7|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/redshoesmargaret0000sull}}\n* {{cite book|last=Tolan|first=Fiona|title=Margaret Atwood: Feminism and Fiction|year=2007|publisher=Rodopi|location=Netherlands|isbn=978-90-420-2223-2}}\n* {{cite book|editor-last1=VanSpanckeren|editor-first1=Kathryn|editor-last2=Castro|editor-first2=Jan Garden|title=Margaret Atwood: Vision and Forms|year=1988|publisher=Southern Illinois University Press|location=Carbondale|isbn=978-0-8093-1408-9}}\n* {{cite book\n|last=Weir\n|first=Lorraine\n|chapter=Meridians of Perception: A Reading of The Journals of Susanna Moodie\n|pages=[https://archive.org/details/artofmargaretatw0000davi/page/69 69\u201379]\n|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/artofmargaretatw0000davi/page/69\n|editor-last1=Davidson\n|editor-first1=Arnold E.\n|editor-last2=Davidson\n|editor-first2=Cathy N.\n|editorlink2=Cathy N. Davidson\n|title=The Art of Margaret Atwood: essays in criticism\n|year=1981\n|location=Toronto\n|publisher=Anansi\n|isbn=978-0-88784-080-7\n|chapter-format=\n|accessdate=\n}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Wrethed|first1=Joakim|title='I am a place': ''Aletheia'' as aesthetic and political resistance in Margaret Atwood's ''Surfacing''|journal=Journal of Aesthetics & Culture|year=2015|volume=7|issue=1|page=28020|doi=10.3402/jac.v7.28020|doi-access=free}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://atwoodsociety.org/ Margaret Atwood Society official website]\n* {{IMDb name|name=Margaret Atwood}}\n* {{isfdb name|n